Trains of them, their hair grown long and dirty from lying in prison, he had ordered to stand before him, to suffer frightful tortures. Here sounded the gratingof the chains they dragged‚ there the crack of leathern lashes, or the crashing of the rods, while the claw pierced the hollow framework of their ribs, laying open deep cavities and tearing their vitals. And now the tormentors were weary and the judge passing into a furious rage at the futility of the trial, for not one of the servants of Christ was found in all the course of their sufferings, who would dare to taint his soul.
